main event: Two bright, elliptical objects were observed traveling at very high speed from northwest to southeast near Warner Robins, Georgia on 23 March 1958.
interesting points: The sighting lasted between 2 to 4 minutes., The objects were reported to be at an altitude of 10,000 ft AGL., The observers were two civilians., The objects were observed moving in a northwest to southeast course., The weather conditions included 3/10 cloud cover with warm temperatures and light winds.
